title: Cracked Tiles - How to Replace
question: #RFI Tiles in bathroom 4a are cracked. How can we replace these without damaging the waterproofing.
suggested_answer: To replace the cracked tiles in bathroom 4a without damaging the waterproofing, follow these steps: 1. Carefully remove the grout around the cracked tiles using a grout saw or rotary tool. 2. Gently lift the cracked tiles using a chisel and hammer, taking care not to damage the underlying waterproofing membrane. 3. Clean the area thoroughly to remove any debris or adhesive residue. 4. Apply a thin layer of waterproof adhesive to the back of the new tiles. 5. Press the new tiles into place and ensure they are level with the surrounding tiles. 6. Allow the adhesive to cure as per the manufacturer's instructions. 7. Reapply grout around the new tiles and seal the grout lines to maintain waterproofing. Suggested actions: Verify the type of waterproofing membrane used and ensure compatibility with the adhesive. Check for any additional manufacturer recommendations for tile replacement.
